hopobject.body: How do you know each other? healthexpressma.com Ms. Merkel could change course. She could, for instance, ease up on austerity, which the Greeks consider punitive, and embrace euro bonds, which would pool some of the debt obligations of the 17 euro zone nations to bring down the funding costs of the struggling countries. Equally, she could harden her austerity and reform demands to the point that Greece and the other bailout victims would have no choice but to ditch the euro and reprint their old currencies.
